      <div class="page-header-main">
        <span class="plate">Sheet 04 / Anti-patterns</span>
        <h1>Not every project needs a <em>blueprint</em>.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          LID has real costs — design before code, review between phases, cascade discipline across changes. When the benefit doesn't outweigh the cost, LID is the wrong choice. Fit problems, not product deficiencies.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="page-header-aside" aria-label="Sheet notes">
        <dl>
          <dt>Sheet</dt>         <dd>04 / 04</dd>
